<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 5:16PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Cascade County through 545 PM MDT...
At 515 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Black Eagle and the east side of Great Falls, moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail. The pea size hail could accumulate up to one
inch deep.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Great Falls, Black Eagle, Malmstrom Afb, Eden, Sand Coulee, Stockett,
Tracy and Centerville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
